# LinkedIn Blog Post: Labs 5 & 6 Release

**December 22, 2025**

---

Last week I released Labs 3 & 4 of Terminus Solutions - the enterprise AWS architecture project I built because I couldn't find what I needed when learning cloud: comprehensive documentation that shows not just what to build, but how companies actually think about infrastructure decisions.


Today, the data and global delivery layers are live.


âœ… **Lab 5: RDS & Database Services**

Multi-AZ RDS MySQL with synchronous replication and automatic failover. Read replicas distributed across AZs for DR. Aurora Serverless variable workloads with auto-scaling capacity. DynamoDB global tables for session management with sub-millisecond latency. ElastiCache Redis.  Secrets Manager with credential rotation. 


âœ… **Lab 6: Route 53 & CloudFront Distribution**

Global CDN. Multi-origin CloudFront architecture serving static content from S3, dynamic content from ALB, and media assets with optimized caching. Origin groups for automatic failover. Route 53 with health checks, latency-based routing, and geolocation policies. AWS WAF at the edge.  Lambda@Edge injecting security headers on every response. SSL/TLS certificates via ACM with auto-renewal.


What makes this different from typical tutorials:


